HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 90
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of Minnesota House Speaker Emerita Melissa Hortman
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives upon the death of Minnesota
3 House Speaker Emerita Melissa Hortman.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the tragic passing of
6 Minnesota House Speaker Emerita Melissa Hortman; and
7 WHEREAS, Melissa Hortman was born on May 27, 1970, in Fridley, Minnesota, and
8 graduated from Blaine High School in 1988; and
9 WHEREAS, Speaker Emerita Hortman attended Boston University, where she
10 majored in philosophy and political science and graduated in 1991; she earned a juris doctor
11 degree from the University of Minnesota Law School and completed a master of public
12 administration degree at the Harvard Kennedy School; and
13 WHEREAS, Speaker Emerita Hortman served in several governmental roles prior
14 to joining the Minnesota Legislature; she was a legislative staffer for U.S. Senators Al Gore
15 and John Kerry; served as a law clerk to Judge John Sommerville in Hennepin County,
16 Minnesota; served on the City Human Relations Commission in Brooklyn Park, Minnesota;
17 and served as an assistant county attorney in Hennepin County; and
18 WHEREAS, Speaker Emerita Hortman was elected to the Minnesota House of
19 Representatives in 2004 and served Anoka and Hennepin Counties; as a legislator, she was
20 active in the areas of transportation, K-12 education funding, higher education, energy, and
21 the environment; and
